title: 2 hurt as magnitude 4.6 quake hits parts of Davao region
text:
Inquirer Mindanao / 11:10 AM February 23, 2017 Map of Davao City and Southern Mindanao 
TAGUM CITY, Davao del Norte â€” A magnitude 4.6 quake struck parts of Southern Mindanao on Thursday morning, state seismologists said, and two persons were hurt in Davao City. 
The tectonic earthquake which occurred at around 9:50 a.m. , was centered some 9 kilometers northwest of Davao City at a depth of 15 kms., the Philippine Institute of Volcanology and Seismology (Phivolcs) said. 
Earthquakes of such magnitude and depth are not expected to cause damage, Phivolcs said. ADVERTISEMENT 
It was felt in Compostela Valley and Davao del Norte provinces, as well as in the cities of Tagum, Panabo and Davao. 
But in Davao City, two persons were injured when a decades-old waiting shed along Quirino Avenue collapsed during the quake. No more details were available as of this posting. 
The Philippines sits on a s0-called Pacific Ring of Fire where continental plates collide, causing frequent quakes and volcanic activity. 
Early this month, a magnitude 6.7 struck Caraga region, causing massive damage in the city of Surigao and killing or wounding over 120 people. SFM/rga
